radiographic_examinations.findings: Minimal bibasilar atelectasis. The appendix is diffusely enlarged, measuring 11 mm, fluid filled with enhancement of the wall, and adjacent fat stranding. No periappendiceal abscess or evidence of perforation is noted. The kidney and pancrease appear normal. There is a small amount of mildly complex free fluid in the pelvis. Prominent lymph nodes in the right lower abdomen.
